        <mxCell id="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-6" value="Logger can be duplicated many times - it must be lightwight - would the Flyweight pattern apply here?" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-615" y="425" width="270" height="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-3" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;endArrow=none;endFill=0;" parent="1" source="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-2" target="TvdYabubaMgP4hZpLByh-5" edge="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-2" value="Implements this class as a Thread-safe singleton. This will allow for the log source configurations to be referenced globally.&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Question:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Can I allow the user to specify their desired log configuration somwhere?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Thought:&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;I can make the Singleton mutable (setSources()), this will need to be synchronised for thread safety. Perhaps a good time to brush up on concurrency and design.&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-685" y="605" width="340" height="190" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="skFjbr4E7Fnc3YblYDC3-5" value="&lt;b&gt;Problem!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I don&#39;t want to have to pass around the LogSources reference to every instance of Logger.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Thought:&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;With a Singleton I wouldn&#39;t have to. I&#39;d just call getInstance and be provided with the instance from anywhere in the application&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Decision:&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;This will only require me to have one single constructor. The sources will be referenced, not passed in. I also then don&#39;t think this will qualify as &quot;composition&quot;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="470" y="440" width="270" height="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
